section.subsection:
Caribbean, located in the Leeward Islands (northern) group;
French part of the island of Saint Martin in the Caribbean Sea;
Saint Martin lies east of the US Virgin Islands

temperature averages 27-29 degrees Celsius all year long; low
humidity, gentle trade winds, brief, intense rain showers;
hurricane season stretches from July to November

excessive population pressure (increasing settlement); waste
management; salinity intrusions into the mainland of the island;
fresh water supply is dependent on desalination of sea water;
over-exploitation of marine resources (reef fisheries, coral and
shell); indiscriminate anchoring of boats damages coral reefs,
causing underwater pollution and sedimentation

